tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic000028.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo R. Henzel, 2016-11-07\" src=\"ISic000028-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of ILMusPalermo</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8417-7089\">Tuuli Ahlholm</a></p>  <p>To Tiberius Claudius Herodianus, a most distinguished man (i.e. of senatorial rank), most extraordinary judge, patron of the colony of Panhormitans. The foremost men (of the colony) gave (this monument) as a gift from communally collected bronze.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 2938 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000352\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000352</a></li><li> Gualtherus 1624 17 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388</a>  </li><li> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 174 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931</a>  </li><li> Mommsen 1883 <a href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650790\" target=\"_blank\">7286</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</a></li><li> Bivona 1970 28 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142</a></li><li> Manganaro 1988 43 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001427</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>Tall, relatively narrow letters, with short horizontal strokes often curving upwards (especially on T).</p> Line 1  95  Line 2  75-80  Line 3  70-75  Line 4-5  65  Line 6  60  Line 7  55  Interlineation line 1 to 2     </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
